<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>EchoStream – Child Safety Standards</title>

  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      background-color: #0b0f19;
      color: #e8eeff;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
    }

    .container {
      max-width: 900px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 32px 20px 60px;
    }

    .card {
      background: #121a2a;
      border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
      border-radius: 14px;
      padding: 28px;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 26px;
      margin-top: 0;
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: 18px;
      margin-top: 28px;
    }

    p, li {
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: rgba(232,238,255,0.9);
    }

    ul {
      padding-left: 20px;
    }

    a {
      color: #7ab7ff;
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }

    .badge {
      display: inline-block;
      background: rgba(122,183,255,0.15);
      border: 1px solid rgba(122,183,255,0.35);
      padding: 6px 12px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      font-size: 14px;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }

    footer {
      margin-top: 28px;
      font-size: 14px;
      color: rgba(232,238,255,0.7);
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="badge">CSAE / Child Safety Policy</div>

      <h1>EchoStream – Child Safety Standards</h1>

      <p>
        EchoStream is committed to protecting children and maintaining a safe platform.
        We enforce a strict zero-tolerance policy toward any content that involves child
        sexual abuse or exploitation (CSAE).
      </p>

      <h2>1. Zero-Tolerance Policy</h2>
      <p>
        EchoStream strictly prohibits any content that depicts, promotes, facilitates,
        or references child sexual abuse or exploitation. This includes:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Sexual content involving minors</li>
        <li>Grooming, solicitation, or exploitation of minors</li>
        <li>Requests for sexual images or interactions involving minors</li>
        <li>Any attempt to direct users to CSAE material</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. Reporting In-App</h2>
      <p>
        Users can report content directly within the EchoStream app using the
        <strong>Report</strong> feature on posts and profiles.
        Reports are reviewed promptly and may result in content removal,
        account suspension, or permanent bans.
      </p>

      <h2>3. External Reporting</h2>
      <p>
        If you believe a child is in immediate danger, contact local emergency services.
        Suspected CSAE can also be reported to the National Center for Missing &
        Exploited Children (NCMEC) CyberTipline:
      </p>

      <p>
        <a href="https://www.missingkids.org/gethelpnow/cybertipline"
           target="_blank"
           rel="noopener noreferrer">
          https://www.missingkids.org/gethelpnow/cybertipline
        </a>
      </p>

      <h2>4. Enforcement</h2>
      <p>
        EchoStream actively monitors and investigates reports of CSAE.
        Violations result in immediate removal of content and permanent account termination.
        Relevant cases may be reported to appropriate authorities.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For questions regarding child safety or compliance, contact:
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Email:</strong>
        <a href="mailto:echosteram@gmail.com">echosteram@gmail.com</a>
      </p>

      <footer>
        Last updated:
        <span id="date"></span>
      </footer>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script>
    document.getElementById("date").textContent =
      new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 10);
  </script>
</body>
</html>
